Ebrahim Ebrahim was sentenced to imprisonment on Robben Island twice during his revolutionary years - something his comrades say displayed his remarkable fortitude after a young life of adversity. In his book titled Beyond Fear, Ebrahim recounts his interrogation and the trial that would send him to Robben Island for the second time. Lindsay Dentlinger reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The memoir of anti-apartheid activist Ebrahim Ebrahim has been launched posthumously in Cape Town. Titled ‘Beyond Fear’, the book documents the former minister’s brushes with the law during the struggle years. WATCH: Ebrahim Ebrahim remembered He died in December aged 84. In his book, Ebrahim recounts his interrogation and the trial that would send him to Robben Island for the second time. * eNCA's Lindsay Dentlinger reports.